“Synapse Surge: Reactive Rhythm Racing – A neurofeedback racing game where the player's brainwaves directly control the vehicle's speed, handling, and power-ups. The game uses advanced EEG sensors to monitor focus, excitement, and relaxation, translating these readings into dynamic in-game effects. High levels of concentration boost acceleration, bursts of adrenaline trigger speed boosts, and calm focus activates defensive shields. Failure to maintain a stable rhythm results in catastrophic crashes. The core mechanic is rhythmic precision - becoming a maestro of your own neural impulses! We can even incorporate haptic feedback – a gentle vibration when you’re in the zone, a jarring pulse when you lose it. Think *F-Zero* meets *Beat Saber*… but with your BRAIN!”